</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/getting-started-with-ekattor-erp/step-7.png\" xss=removed></li><li><span xss=\"removed\">If you have reached to this page, </span><span xss=\"removed\">Congratulations!</span><span xss=\"removed\"> You have installed Ekattor Successfully.</span></li></ul>', 1),
(11, 14, '<p xss=\"removed\">Once you\'ve installed the application, You are good to go.</p><p xss=\"removed\">But before that make it yours. </p><p xss=\"removed\">Go to <b>Settings > System Settings</b> option and provide all the Settings data before starting to use the application.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-setup/settings-setup.png\" xss=\"removed\"></p><p xss=\"removed\"><br></p><p xss=\"removed\">Go to <b>Settings > School Settings</b> option and provide all the basic school\'s data.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-setup/school-setup.png\" xss=\"removed\"></p><p xss=\"removed\">You can also create and select <b>Current Academic Session</b> before using the application. Just go to <b>Back Office > Session Manager</b> option.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-setup/session-setup.png\" xss=\"removed\"><br></p>', 1),
(12, 15, '<p xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d4e4ca60-7fff-ff71-c36e-178840ba891d\" xss=\"removed\">Inside Class module, Superadmin or Admin will get all the list of created class.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d4e4ca60-7fff-ff71-c36e-178840ba891d\" xss=\"removed\">Superadmin or Admin can add new class and can edit and delete from this module.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d4e4ca60-7fff-ff71-c36e-178840ba891d\" xss=\"removed\">Inside Class table there is a button for managing Section. Superadmin or Admin can Create, edit and delete Section for that specific class.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d4e4ca60-7fff-ff71-c36e-178840ba891d\" xss=\"removed\"><br></span><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-setup/class-and-section.png\" xss=\"removed\"></p>', 1),
(13, 16, '<div xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Head over to the ClassRoom section from <span xss=\"removed\">Academic > Class Room</span>.</span></div><div xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">You can create new Classrooms there.</span></div><div xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">You can also Edit and Delete the existing Classrooms.</span></div><div xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><br></span><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-setup/classrooms.png\" xss=\"removed\"></div>', 1),
(14, 17, '<p xss=removed><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9671d2c9-7fff-519c-f983-b9fe70140817\" xss=removed>Every Teacher belongs to a specific Department. So before creating a Teacher it is important to know, how to create Departments first.</span></p><p xss=removed><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9671d2c9-7fff-519c-f983-b9fe70140817\" xss=removed>Get the Department list from Department section. You will find the Department section inside Academic section.</span></p><p xss=removed><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9671d2c9-7fff-519c-f983-b9fe70140817\" xss=removed>Click on Department option and you will get the list of created Departments. Click on Add Department button from the top and you will have a form for creating new Departments.</span></p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/academics/departments.png\" xss=removed><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-9671d2c9-7fff-519c-f983-b9fe70140817\" xss=removed><br></span></p>', 1),
(15, 18, '<p xss=removed>Teacher is one of the key features of a School management system. You can create Teachers by following few minimal steps here.</p><p xss=removed>Before creating teacher make sure that you have created Departments first. Because every teacher belongs to a specific department.</p><p xss=removed>If you are all set, Move to Teacher option from Users section from the left side menu.</p><p xss=removed>You will get all the teacher list there. If you want to create new one, Click on the Create Teacher button from the top. Fill the fields and submit the form. It will provide you a success message.</p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/academics/teachers.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(16, 19, '<p xss=removed>You can add Syllabuses which will be available on Student and Parent panel.</p><p xss=removed>For adding a new Syllabus, go to Syllabus option from <b>Academic</b> section. Click on the <b>Add Syllabus</b> button.</p><div><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/academics/syllabus.png\" xss=removed><br></div>', 1),
(17, 20, '<p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">There are 3 ways to admit a student into Ekattor.</span></p><ol xss=\"removed\"><li><span xss=\"removed\">Single Student Admission.</span></li><li><span xss=\"removed\">Bulk Student Admission.</span></li><li><span xss=\"removed\">Student Admission by Uploading CSV File.</span></li></ol><p xss=\"removed\"><b>Single Student Admission:</b></p><p xss=\"removed\">    If the number of student to register is very low, you can choose this option.</p><p xss=\"removed\">    This way you have to put all the data related to student and submit the form.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/admission/single.png\" xss=\"removed\"></p><p xss=\"removed\"><b>Bulk Student Admission:</b><br></p><p xss=\"removed\">    <span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">If the number of student to register is not tiny, you can choose this option.</span><br></span></p><p xss=\"removed\">    This way you can put multiple student\'s data at a time. That means you can admit more that one student by this option.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/admission/bulk.png\" xss=\"removed\"></p><p xss=\"removed\"><b>Student Admission by Uploading CSV File:</b><br></p><p xss=\"removed\">   <span xss=\"removed\"> </span><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">If the number of student to register is huge, This option will save a lot of time and efforts.</span><br></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"></p><h5 xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"></span></h5><p xss=\"removed\"></p><p xss=\"removed\">    This way you can upload a CSV( Comma Separated Value )file and get all the user as registered.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/admission/excel.png\" xss=\"removed\"><br></p>', 1),
(18, 21, '<p xss=removed>User management is the key and most basic feature of a management system. In Ekattor there are 7 different user roles. Superadmin, Admin, Teacher, Parent, Student, Accountant and Librarian.</p><p xss=removed>Every user role has its own specific task to do.</p><p xss=removed>The Super admin role has all the privileges like creating admins and installing addons and so on. Superadmin is the highest authority of this system.</p><p xss=removed>You can find role wise user list from Users section of left side navigation menu.</p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/user-management/users.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(19, 22, '<p xss=removed>Ekattor now provides Super Admin and Admins the ability to allocate Teacher\'s task permission.</p><p xss=removed>Just choose the Class and Section and enable or disable the task permission. It\'s that simple.</p><p xss=removed><b>For example:</b> If enable Attendance permission of a teacher  for Class One and Section A, he will be able to manage attendance for that specific class and section\'s Student.</p><p xss=removed>Go to Users section and choose Teacher Permission.</p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/teacher-permission/permission.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(20, 23, '<p xss=removed>Ekattor makes it easier to keep track of Student\'s attendance report.</p><p xss=removed>Go to Daily Attendance option from Academic section of left side menu.</p><p xss=removed>Choose desire Month, Year, Class and Section. Hit Filter button. It will generate the attendance report for that specific class\'s student.</p><p xss=removed>You can also print the attendance report.</p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/attendance/attendance.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(21, 24, '<p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Ekattor\'s Class Routine module has been helping schools to schedule and manage week based class timing.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Student and Parent also get the class routing on their panel. It helps them to know the class timing for an entire week.</span></p>', 1),
(22, 25, '<p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Admin and Super admin can create class routines. From the Academic section you will get the Class Routine option.</span><br></p><p xss=removed><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Droid Sans, sans-serif\">By clicking on the Class Routine option, it will take you to the class routine view.</font></p><p xss=removed><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Droid Sans, sans-serif\">From there you can create Class routine for a specific class.</font></p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/class-routine/class-routine.png\" xss=removed><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Droid Sans, sans-serif\"><br></font></p>', 1),
(23, 26, '<p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Schools event schedules can be maintained in Ekattor\'s Event Calendar.</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Where the Students, Parents, Teachers can check the upcoming and past events.</span></p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/event-calendar/event-calendar.png\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed><br></span></p>', 1),
(24, 27, '<p xss=removed>There are two types of Event Calendars. One will only be shown in Backend and the other will only be shown in Frontend.</p><p xss=removed>If you want to create a backend event on Event Calendar, Go to Academic section and choose Event Calendar option.</p><p xss=removed>You will find <b>Add New Event </b>Button there.</p><p xss=removed>For creating events only for Frontend, please check out our <b>School Website</b> documentation.</p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/event-calendar/event-calendar-admin.png\"><br></p>', 1),
(25, 28, '<p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">In Ekattor managing Exams and Marks have been easier than before.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">User can set up Grading systems according to their preferences there.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\">It is <span xss=\"removed\">flexible for teachers to enter marks and update it whenever necessary.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/exam-and-grades/marks.png\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\"><br></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/exam-and-grades/grades.png\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\"><br></span></p>', 1),
(26, 29, '<p xss=removed><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b1e03dd6-7fff-4615-66f5-06c2bc2ab6c5\" xss=removed>For promoting student, you have to head over to Promotion menu from the left navigation bar. Select Current Session, Select next session where you want to promote the student, Select the class of the student and select the class where the students are promoting. After clicking on Manage Promotion button, you will get the list of Student and button for promoting that specific student.</span></p><p xss=removed><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b1e03dd6-7fff-4615-66f5-06c2bc2ab6c5\" xss=removed>Visual representation will make thing easier to understand.</span></p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/student-promotion/promotion.png\" xss=removed><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b1e03dd6-7fff-4615-66f5-06c2bc2ab6c5\" xss=removed><br></span></p>', 1),
(27, 30, '<p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Click on the Student Fee Manager option from Accounting  section. You will find a list of created invoices.</span><br></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">You can create new invoices from here also.</span><br></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">On the top there are two buttons for creating student fees. You can create Mass Invoices for a certain class or you can create Single Invoice for particular students.</span><br></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Checkout the screenshot below, it will help you to understand more.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><b>Created Academic Fees:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/accounting/invoices.png\" xss=\"removed\"></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><br></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><b>Creating Single Invoice for Student:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/accounting/single-invoice.png\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\"><b><br></b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><b><br></b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><b>Creating Mass Invoices for a Class\'s Students:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/accounting/mass-invoices.png\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\"><b><br></b><br></span></p>', 1),
(28, 31, '<p xss=\"removed\">Student and Parent can pay the academic fees from their user panel.</p><p xss=\"removed\">After logging into their account, they will get an option name Student Fee manager.</p><p xss=\"removed\">They will be able to pay only the unpaid invoices. They can also have the printed copy of Paid invoices.</p><p xss=\"removed\">By default user can pay with Paypal and Stripe payment gateways.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/accounting/pay-fees.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(29, 32, '<p xss=removed>Expenses become easy to track down on Ekattor.</p><p xss=removed>Admin, Superadmin and Accountants are the user roles who will be able to manage the Expenses.</p><p xss=removed>Every expense should belong to a specific Expense category.</p><p xss=removed>New expenses can be added from here too.</p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/accounting/expenses.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(30, 33, '<p xss=removed>Managing Accounting report is one of the most crucial features for a School manager.</p><p xss=removed>In Ekattor we <span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>gave special importance</span> on the Accounting section.</p><p xss=removed>That\'s why we\'ve come up with an elegant and easy to understand user interface of Accounting.</p><p xss=removed>Admin and Accountants can get the accounting reports with a certain date range, can filter the reports according to a specific class or payment status.</p><p xss=removed>All the data can be exported as CSV (<span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Comma Separated Values</span><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>) file or as PDF file or can print the data.</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Take a look on the report export view.</span></p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/accounting/export-report.png\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed><br></span></p>', 1),
(31, 34, '<p xss=removed>Using library manager, Librarian or Admin can organize and manage books with all details available for the books.</p><p xss=removed>Librarian can add new books to the library , or they can edit and delete those also.</p><p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Students can search the book details from their dashboard.</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Student can check whether the book is available to issue from there dashboard.</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed><b>Library Manager:</b></span></p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/library-manager/library.png\" xss=removed></p><p xss=removed><br></p><p xss=removed><b>Issued Books Manager:</b></p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/library-manager/book-issue.png\" xss=removed><b><br></b><br></p><div><br></div>', 1),
(32, 35, '<p xss=removed>Noticeboard module helps admins to manage notices.</p><p xss=removed>By default current month notices will be shown on backend or user panel. But on the website all the upcoming notices will be shown date wise.</p><p xss=removed>Admin and Superadmin can create notices from Noticeboard menu of Back Office section.</p><p xss=removed>Just click on the specific date and Notice creation form will be popped up.</p><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/noticeboard/notices.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(33, 36, '<p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Every school should have a website. In that case, Ekattor is a complete school management solution.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Ekattor does not provide only the backend user panel but also provides an elegant website. </span></p><p xss=\"removed\">Which can be managed from backend.</p><p xss=\"removed\">Ekattor has a huge Website Settings module. Superadmin can manage every items on frontend website by simply updating stuffs.</p><p xss=\"removed\">It will be better if you have a visual representation of it. We\'ve attached couple of them.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><b>General Settings:</b></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-website-settings/general-settings.png\" xss=removed><b><br></b></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=removed><b>Slider Settings:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-website-settings/homepage-slider.png\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=removed><b>Frontend Events Settings:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-website-settings/website-events.png\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=removed><b>Terms and Conditions:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-website-settings/terms-and-conditions.png\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=removed><b>Frontend Gallery:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/school-website-settings/gallery.png\" xss=removed><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span><b><br></b></p>', 1),
(34, 37, '<p xss=\"removed\">Ekattor is Multi Language supported application.</p><p><span xss=\"removed\">Superadmin can create as many language as he/she wants.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"></p><p xss=\"removed\">Just go to Language Settings option from Settings section and you can create new languages.</p><p xss=\"removed\">You can also update the phrases as per your preferences.</p><p xss=\"removed\">After creating language you can update the phrase by simply clicking on Update Phrase sub-menu.</p><p xss=\"removed\"><b>Language List:</b></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/multi-language/languages.png\" xss=\"removed\"><b><br></b></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><b>Update Phrase of A Particular Language:</b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/multi-language/update-phrases.png\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><b><br></b></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=removed><b>Update Phrase Form:</b></span></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/multi-language/phrases.png\" xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=removed><b><br></b></span><b><br></b></span><b><br></b></p>', 1),
(35, 38, '<p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Ekattor supports multiple user role login.</span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Teacher is one of them.<br></span></p><p xss=removed><span xss=\"removed\" xss=removed>Each Teacher will be given a unique login credentials and can perform activities based on the privileges assigned by the system.</span></p><ul xss=removed><li><span xss=\"removed\">Teacher can see all the Student\'s and Teacher\'s list.</span></li><li>Teacher can take attendance of his assigned classes only. Admin and Superadmin will be able to set the permission to teacher\'s task. Which has been discussed on Teacher permission module.</li><li>Teacher can checkout the Class Routines, Subjects of any classes.</li><li>Teacher can also checkout Event Calendar, Exams, Library etc.</li><li>Teacher can add Syllabus for a particular class.</li><li>Providing Marks for assigned class is also another task for Teacher role.</li></ul><h5 xss=removed>Teacher\'s Dashboard:</h5><p xss=removed><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/teacher-panel/teacher-panel.png\" xss=removed><br></p>', 1),
(36, 39, '<p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Once the Admin has admitted all the students, they </span><span xss=\"removed\">will be given a unique login credentials and can perform activities based on the privileges assigned by the system.</span></p><ul><li><span xss=\"removed\"></span><span xss=\"removed\">Students can:</span></li><ul><li>Keep track of their daily attendance.</li><li>Check Class Routines.</li><li>Download Syllabuses, which was uploaded by Admin, Teachers.</li><li>Know about the upcoming events by having an Event Calendar.<br></li><li>Check their acquired Marks and Grades.</li><li>Check their Academic Fee Reports.</li><li>Pay the unpaid Academic Fees.</li><li>Generate printed copy of paid invoices.</li><li>Check the available books for issuing.</li></ul></ul><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">For knowing more, you can go to our demo application.</span></p>', 1),
(37, 40, '<p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Once the Admin has created Parents, they </span><span xss=removed>will be given a unique login credentials and can perform activities based on the privileges assigned by the system.</span></p><ul><li xss=removed>Parents<span xss=removed> can:</span></li><ul><li>Keep track of their <span xss=\"removed\">children</span>\'s daily attendance.</li><li>Check their children\'s Class Routines.</li><li>Download Syllabuses, which was uploaded by Admin, Teachers.</li><li>Know about the upcoming events by having an Event Calendar.<br></li><li>Check their acquired Marks and Grades of their children\'s.</li><li>Check their Academic Fee Reports.</li><li>Pay the unpaid Academic Fees.</li><li>Generate printed copy of paid invoices.</li><li>Check the available books for issuing.</li></ul></ul><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>For knowing more, you can go to our demo application.</span></p>', 1),
(38, 41, '<p><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Once the Accountant has been created, they </span><span xss=removed>will be given a unique login credentials and can perform activities based on the privileges assigned by the system.</span></p></p><ul><li xss=removed><span xss=removed>Accountant</span><span xss=removed> can:</span></li><ul><li>Manage student\'s Academic Fees.</li><li>Generate accounting reports.M</li><li>Manage Expenses of a School.</li><li>Manage Expense Categories of a School.</li><li>Creating and Updating invoices.<br></li></ul></ul><p xss=removed><span xss=removed>For knowing more, you can go to our demo application.</span></p>', 1),
(39, 42, '<div>Once the Librarian has been created, they will be given a unique login credentials and can perform activities based on the privileges assigned by the system.</div><div><br></div><ul><li>Librarians can:</li><ul><li>Add new books on Library</li><li>Edit existing books.</li><li>Issue book for Student.</li><li>For knowing more, you can go to our demo application.</li></ul></ul>', 1),
(40, 43, '<div>Sometimes single School Admin can not be enough to manage an entire school. Multiple School Admins can help on that.</div><div><br></div><div>Superadmin is the one who can manage those Admins.</div><div><br></div><div>Superadmin can Create, Update or Delete admins for a specific school.</div><div><br></div><div>School Admin will not get all the privileges like Superadmin does. But they will get most of them.</div><div><br></div><div>Take a look on the School Admins list page below,</div><div><img src=\"https://creativeitem.com/v2/uploads/documentation/ekattor-erp/multiple-school-admin/admins.png\" xss=removed><br></div>', 1),
(41, 11, '<p>Ekattor school management system ERP is an online platform where <span style=\"font-family: Nunito;\">﻿</span>authorities can operate daily activities and control school data.<br></p><p style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Student admissions, Student management, Admin management, Permission attributing, Exam management, Fees management, Accounting management, Library management, Teacher management, Parents management are included in the routine activities. Ekattor school management system ERP is helpful for:&nbsp;</span></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Schools&nbsp;</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Colleges&nbsp;</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Universities&nbsp;</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Other educational institutions etc.</span></li></ul>', 1);

