(47, 52, '<p>Mastery LMS operates on a subscription system every Month / Year / Number of days. By purchasing a subscription package to this LMS, the users can access all classes of the site. It will make your website more attractive and greatly help users to keep up.</p><p><span xss=\"removed\">You can create free classes and individually free lessons by Mastery. The lesson playing page is very user-friendly at Mastery. Students can discuss their problems with others, add class reviews, and follow the instructor at the same place.</span><br></p>', 1),
(48, 51, '<p style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Please follow the below steps to complete the installation process.</span></p><p style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><br></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Upload​ ​the​ ​downloaded​ ​zip​ ​file​ ​from​ ​CodeCanyon​ ​to​ ​your​ ​server</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">You​ ​can​ ​upload​ ​anywhere​ ​inside​ ​your​ ​​public_html​​ ​folder​ ​or​ ​any​ ​sub-folder you​ ​want. ​Just​ ​keep​ ​in​ ​mind​ ​the​ ​directory​ ​where​ ​you​ ​have​ ​uploaded​ ​it.</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Unzip​ ​the​ ​file.</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Go​ ​to​ ​your​ ​preferred​ ​web​ ​browser​ ​and​ ​type​ ​the​ URL​ ​where​ ​you​ ​have unzipped​ ​the​ ​file.​ For​ ​example​ ​-​ ​if​ ​you​ ​have​ ​a​ ​domain​ example.com​ ​ ​you have to​ ​unzip​ ​the​ ​files​ ​inside​ ​a​ ​folder​ ​\"</span><strong style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">mastery</strong><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">,\"​ ​the​ URL​ ​will​ ​be ​example.com/mastery.</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">After​ ​you​ ​have​ ​entered​ ​the​ URL​ ​on​ ​your​ ​browser​ ​will​ ​see​ ​the​ ​screen​ ​below.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><br></p><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/mastery-lms/installation/installation-process.png\" title=\"Installation Process\" alt=\"Installation Process\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Installation Process\" alt=\"Installation Process\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Figure 1.</span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mastery LMS Starting Installation Process</span></span></h5><h5><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br></span></span></h5><ul style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Before starting the installation process, you will need to have the CodeCanyon purchase code, the database name, database username, database password, and database host. You can get the purchase code from your purchase information on CodeCanyon, for having the database information, you will need to create a new database on your server. You will also need to make sure that the files in /application/config/database.php and /application/config/routes.php have to write permission. You should also check if PHP curl is enabled on your server or not.</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">After you hit the \"</span><strong style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Start Installation Process</strong><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">\" button you will see the screen below.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><br></p><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/mastery-lms/installation/continue-the-installation.png\" title=\"Continue The Installation\" alt=\"Continue The Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Continue The Installation\" alt=\"Continue The Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Figure 2.</span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mastery LMS Continue Installation Process</span></span></h5><h5><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br></span></span></h5><ul style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">This screen checks if the required files have the write permission and curl is enabled or not. If these are not enabled, you will face issues in the installation process. So make sure that all the three points on that screen have a green checkmark. If everything is fine and you hit the \"</span><strong style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Continue</strong><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">\" button will be presented with this screen.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><br></p><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/mastery-lms/installation/purchase-code.png\" title=\"Purchase Code\" alt=\"Purchase Code\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Purchase Code\" alt=\"Purchase Code\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Figure 3.</span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mastery LMS Providing Purchase Code</span></span></h5><h5><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br></span></span></h5><ul style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Here you will need to insert the purchase code that you have got from CodeCanyon and hit the \"</span><strong style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Continue</strong><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">\" button which will lead you to the screen below.</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Here you will need to insert your previously created database credentials correctly. The installer will check if the information is correct after you hit the \"</span><strong style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Continue</strong><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">\" button, and if everything is fine, you will be directed to the page below.&nbsp;</span></li><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">After the installer has successfully imported the database, you will get the following page.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><br></p><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/mastery-lms/installation/database-connection.png\" title=\"Database Connection\" alt=\"Database Connection\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Database Connection\" alt=\"Database Connection\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed40108f-7fff-ed2c-30d7-1f260085ca2b\"><span xss=\"removed\"><br></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed40108f-7fff-ed2c-30d7-1f260085ca2b\"><span xss=\"removed\"></span></span></p><h5><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Figure 4.</span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mastery LMS Providing Database Connection Details</span></span></h5><h5><br></h5><ul style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background: transparent; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt;\"><li style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; list-style-type: disc;\"><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Fill up the information required and hit the button \"</span><strong style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">Set me up</strong><span style=\"background: transparent; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">.\" This will save your school name and administrator login credentials which will be required later for logging in to the application and will present the following page.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed40108f-7fff-ed2c-30d7-1f260085ca2b\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c46d6cfa-7fff-5a73-d528-7e79bdb27c2c\"></span></span><span xss=\"removed\"><br></span></span></p>', 1),
(49, 53, '', 1),
(50, 59, '<p><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Academy LMS generally works with three types of users. Admins,&nbsp;</span><span xss=\"removed\">instructors,</span><span xss=\"removed\">&nbsp;and students, if you are the lone instructor of your course portal, allowing public instructors increases the number of instructors to three. There are three different user roles in the academy LMS: administrator, students, and instructor.</span></span></p><p><span xss=\"removed\">The Academy LMS application strives to provide the most excellent possible user experience. Academy LMS has a user-friendly and transparent workflow. All you have to do is follow the steps below:</span></p><h3><span xss=\"removed\">Installation:</span></h3><p></p><p><font xss=\"removed\">The first thing you need to do is download the Academy LMS application file from CodeCanyon. Then follow the instructions, install Academy LMS on your cPanel.</font></p><h3><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Configuration:</span></span></span></h3><p><span xss=\"removed\">Following the installation, you must configure the academy LMS for your website. Then, to launch this program, you must specify all of the basic settings with all relevant data.</span></p><p></p><h3><span xss=\"removed\">Creating the Course:</span></h3><p></p><p><span xss=\"removed\">After installation and setup, an instructor is ready to construct a course or lecture to distribute. Instructors can create lessons by providing documents, pictures, and videos according to their expertise. In addition, the academy LMS delivers one of the best course editors to make the course more engaging and informative.</span></p><h3><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Enroll and Sales:&nbsp;</span></span></h3><p></p><p><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">An instructor is ready to give his lesson after creating the course with the aid of the academy LMS course editor. The course can then be purchased and enrolled in by students, workers, or end-users. When they purchase the courses, the administrator and instructor begin making money by selling the students\' approach and developing a career.</span></span></span></p><h3><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span xss=\"removed\">Learning from the Course:</span></span></span></span></h3><p></p><p><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Students, workers, or end-users can begin studying from the course after purchasing it. They can receive a variety of distinctive benefits from Academy LMS. Learners, for example, receive an advanced course player, track their progress in the course, save courses to their wishlist, and contact the instructor\'s assistance. They may also sort and filter the course list, log in securely, and create a personal account. Academy consistently offers a pleasant user experience.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></p><p><br></p>', 1),
(51, 60, '<p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Please follow the below steps to complete the installation process.&nbsp;</span></p><ul xss=\"removed\"><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Upload​ ​the​ ​downloaded​ ​zip(Academy-LMS.zip)​ ​file​ ​from​ ​CodeCanyon​ ​to​ ​your​ ​server&nbsp;</span></li><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">You​ ​can​ ​upload​ ​anywhere​ ​inside​ ​your​ ​​public_html​​ ​folder​ ​or​ ​any​ ​sub-folder you​ ​want. ​Just​ ​keep​ ​in​ ​mind​ ​the​ ​directory​ ​where​ ​you are.​&nbsp;</span></li><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Unzip​ ​the​ ​file.&nbsp;</span></li><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Go​ ​to​ ​your​ ​preferred​ ​web​ ​browser​ ​and​ ​type​ ​the​ ​URL​ ​where​ ​you​ ​have the files.</span></li></ul><p><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><b>Example:</b> example.com/Academy-LMS</span></p><ul><li><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span xss=\"removed\">Unzipped​ ​the​ ​file.​ For​ ​example​ ​-​ ​if​ ​you​ ​have​ ​a​ ​domain​ example.com​ ​and​ ​​ ​unzipped​ ​the​ ​files​ ​inside​ ​a​ ​folder​ ​\"<b>Academy</b>,\"​ ​the​ ​URL​ ​will​ ​be ​example.com/academy.</span><span xss=\"removed\">&nbsp;</span><br></span></li><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">After​ ​you​ ​have​ ​entered​ ​the​ ​URL​ ​on​ ​your​ ​browser​ ​will​ ​see​ ​the​ ​screen​ ​below.&nbsp;</span></li></ul><p xss=\"removed\"><br></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/academy-lms/getting-started/academy-start-installation.png\" title=\"Academy Start Installation\" alt=\"Academy Start Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Academy Start Installation\" alt=\"Academy Start Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"><span style=\"background: transparent; text-align: inherit; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 0.875rem; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><b>Figure 1.</b></span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"background: transparent; text-align: inherit; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 0.875rem; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">&nbsp;Academy LMS starting installation</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"background: transparent; text-align: inherit; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 0.875rem; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><br></span></p><ul xss=\"removed\"><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">The first step is installation. Before starting,&nbsp;</span>you will need to have the CodeCanyon purchase code, the database name, username, password, and database host in the installation process. You can get the purchase code from your purchase information on codecanyon. For having the database information, you will need to create a new database on your server. You will also need to ensure that the files in /application/config/database.php and /application/config/routes.php have written permission. You should also verify if your server has PHP CURL enabled. after you hit the \"<b>Start Installation Process</b>\" button, you will see the screen below.&nbsp;</span></li></ul><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/academy-lms/getting-started/academy-installation-curl-enabled.png\" title=\"Academy Installation Curl Enabled\" alt=\"Academy Installation Curl Enabled\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Academy Installation Curl Enabled\" alt=\"Academy Installation Curl Enabled\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span style=\"font-size: 0.9375rem; background: transparent; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">F</span><span style=\"font-size: 0.9375rem; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">igure 2</span><span style=\"font-size: 0.9375rem; background: transparent; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">.</span><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"font-size: 0.9375rem; background: transparent; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;Academy LMS installation Curl Enabled</span></h5><h5><span data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"font-size: 0.9375rem; background: transparent; color: rgb(14, 16, 26); margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; font-weight: normal;\"><br></span></h5><h4><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">This screen checks if the required files have the write permission and curl is enabled or not. If these are not allowed, you will face issues in the installation process. So make sure that all the three points on that screen have a green checkmark. If everything is fine and you hit the \"Continue\" button will be presented with this screen.&nbsp;</span></h4><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/academy-lms/getting-started/academy-installtion-purchasc-code.png\" title=\"Academy Installtion Purchasc Code\" alt=\"Academy Installtion Purchasc Code\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Academy Installtion Purchasc Code\" alt=\"Academy Installtion Purchasc Code\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Figure 3. <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Academy LMS installation purchase code</span></span></span></h5><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br></span></span></span></h5><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Here you will need to insert the purchase code that you have got from CodeCanyon and hit the \"<b>Continue</b>\" button, which will lead you to the screen below.&nbsp;</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><br></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/academy-lms/getting-started/academy-database-installation.png\" title=\"Academy Database Installation\" alt=\"Academy Database Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Academy Database Installation\" alt=\"Academy Database Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Figure 4. <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Academy LMS database installation</span></span></span></h5><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br></span></span></span></h5><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Here you will need to insert your previously created database credentials correctly. The installer will check if the information is correct after you hit the \"<b>Continue\"</b>&nbsp;button, and if everything is fine, You will direct to the page below.</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><br></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/academy-lms/getting-started/academy-database-successfully-installation.png\" title=\"Academy Database Successfully Installation\" alt=\"Academy Database Successfully Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Academy Database Successfully Installation\" alt=\"Academy Database Successfully Installation\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Figure 5. <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Academy LMS successfully installation</span></span></span></h5><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br></span></span></span></h5><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"></span></p><ul xss=\"removed\"><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">&nbsp;You have to click the Install button, automatically importing the application database to your created database. It may take a while, according to your server performance. Would you please wait while the import process a completed?&nbsp;</span></li><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">After the installer has successfully imported the database, you will get the following page.&nbsp;</span></li></ul><h5><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/academy-lms/getting-started/academy-installation-successfull.png\" title=\"Academy Installation Successfull\" alt=\"Academy Installation Successfull\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Academy Installation Successfull\" alt=\"Academy Installation Successfull\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-size: 0.9375rem; text-align: inherit; white-space: nowrap;\">Figure 6.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-size: 0.9375rem; text-align: inherit; white-space: nowrap;\"> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Academy LMS uploading data</span></span></h5><h5><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-size: 0.9375rem; text-align: inherit; white-space: nowrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br></span></span></h5><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span xss=\"removed\">Fill up the information required and hit the button \"<b>Set me up</b>.\" It will save your school name and administrator login credentials later needed for logging into the application and present the following page.&nbsp;</span></span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/creativeitem.com/uploads/documentation/academy-lms/getting-started/academy-installation-success.png\" title=\"Academy Installation Success\" alt=\"Academy Installation Success\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\"\" title=\"Academy Installation Success\" alt=\"Academy Installation Success\" style=\"max-width : 100%;\" \"=\"\" xss=\"removed\"></p><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Figure 7. <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Academy LMS logging in to the server&nbsp;</span></span></span></h5><h5><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br></span></span></span></h5><ul xss=\"removed\"><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">Now hit the \"<b>Login</b>\" button, which will redirect you to the backend of the application, where you will be able to log in as an administrator using the email and password you have entered in the previous step.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li><li xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><span xss=\"removed\">Would you please make sure to go through all the steps chronologically? Otherwise, the installation might fail, and you will face issues running the application. For any help, contact</span><span xss=\"removed\"> ​</span></span><a xss=\"removed\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://support.creativeitem.com/\" class=\"editor-rtfLink\">Creativeitem Support Center</a><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\">.&nbsp;</span></li></ul><h3><span xss=\"removed\"><br></span></h3><h3><span xss=\"removed\">Product Update Instructions​<b> ​</b></span></h3><p></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">You are already running the application. Would you please go through the file update_instructions.txt, which will be in the product\'s downloaded copy in the \"<b>updater</b>\" folder? All the necessary information required to update the product successfully will be there.&nbsp;</span></p><p xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\" data-preserver-spaces=\"true\"><br></span></p>', 1);
